	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-03-07T01:14:25">Bahamas Petroleum Company plc is an Isle of Man-based oil and gas exploration company. The Company is engaged in the exploration of oil and gas. The Company owns a 100% offshore licenses exclusively focused on the commonwealth of The Bahamas. The Company is focused on evaluating and realizing the potential of a range of carbonate reservoir systems contained in operated leases in Bahamian waters. The Company was formed to invest in an offshore oil exploration programme in license areas covering approximately 16,000 square kilometers (four million acres) in the territorial waters and maritime Exclusive Economic Zone (EEZ) of The Bahamas. The Company holds 100% interests through its wholly owned subsidiaries in five exploration Licenses.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-07-23T10:48:52">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Bahamas Petroleum Company PLC revenues was not reported. Net loss decreased 5% to $2.3M. Lower net loss reflects Other Expenses decrease of 4% to $1.3M (expense), Employee benefit expense decrease of 5% to $1M (expense), Depreciation expense decrease of 27% to $27K (expense).</Text>
